==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foreground
<hw>Fore"ground`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>On a painting,
and sometimes in a bas-relief, mosaic picture, or the like, that part of
the scene represented, which is nearest to the spectator, and therefore
occupies the lowest part of the work of art itself. Cf.
<er>Distance</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, 6.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreguess</ent>⟦br⟧
